{0 Backends}

Backend layers consume canonical proof views and produce verifier-facing
artifacts, mainly for Why3.

{1 Scope}

Backend code translates already-constructed obligations into target formats.
It should not redefine source semantics; it compiles semantic IR into backend
artifacts.

{1 Main areas in the repository}

- `lib/adapters/out/backends/why3`
  Why3 translation, runtime views, and backend planning.

- `lib/domain/middleend/proof_export`
  Proof-kernel export data consumed for interop and guided flows.

{1 Notes}

The Why3 backend is driven by canonical obligations and proof views emitted by
the middle-end. Generated Why code is a compilation artifact.
